import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    cuisine_type = data['key'].value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False)
    if len(cuisine_type) > 20:
        cuisine_type = cuisine_type[:20]
    ax = cuisine_type.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('Cuisine Type')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common cuisine type in the University District?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=45)
    ax.yaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(integer=True))
    for i in ax.patches:
        ax.text(i.get_x()+.05, i.get_height()+.5, str(round(i.get_height(), 2)), fontsize=10)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude values for restaurants in the University District?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))

    plt.xticks(rotation=90)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
